          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The price is from the year 2023. The price is estimated as a proxy based on the source: https://ag.umass.edu/sites/ag.umass.edu/files/pdf-doc-ppt/potato_budget.xls. The prices were adjusted for inflation relative to 2005 using the producer price index (PPI) of the euro area, published by eurostat (https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/STS_INPP_A__custom_6416181/default/table?lang=en, last accessed on 2023-06-01).</comment>
        </property>
        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">The production volume is a 3-year-average from 2019 to 2021 for the US. It is assumed that the amount of produced potatoes equals to amount of graded potatoes. Source: FAOSTAT. Crops and livestock products. Available (accessed 6/10/2023): https://www.fao.org/faostat/en/#data</productionVolumeComment>
